args: Who put ya up to this, punk?!
I don't need to tell you anything!\nDie!
Foul wyrmbind, show me your power!\nRaaaaaagh!
What do you think? You know I only care\nabout the Syndicate.
Ah, right... The organization that\nfused your body with a dragon's.
What, so this goon was one'a theirs?
Looks like they've got plans to snuff\nyou out.
The Syndicate is after ME?\nWhat could that mean?
I don't know. But since it's come to this,\nI'm going to be spending some time\nat the Halidom.
Thank you, Aldred.\nYou're welcome to stay as long as you like.
Don't get it twisted. I just don't want you\nin my way while I'm out sniffing for leads.
Ha! Stubborn little skid mark, ain't he?
Whoa, Cleo! Take a breath.\nWho do you mean?
Ha ha ha. Turns out he's one weird\nlittle dude.
What happened?\nDid he do something at the castle?
Oh, you shall see soon enough.
Hey. Have you seen any suspicious\npeople lurking around?
Hmph. Well, someone stole food\nfrom the stores not too long ago. \nRing any bells?
Huh. Beats me. Definitely wasn't your ol'\npal Ranzal, at least!
If nobody knows, then it HAS to\nbe the work of the Syndicate!
What? That seems like a stretch.
Tch. Where are you, Syndicate cowards?!
Hey, Aldred? The Syndicate isn't\naround—aaand he's gone.
I'm guessing this is what you were\ntalking about earlier.
Yes. No matter how big or small,\nhe seems to perceive every problem\nas some sinister Syndicate plot.
Exhibit A: I hung some laundry out to dry,\nand when a sudden breeze blew it away,\nhe said, ＂The Syndicate strikes again!＂
Y'know, it's kinda easy to pity the poor\nkid, depending on how ya look at it.
He's been sleepin' with one eye open\nhis whole damn life.
You're right. The Syndicate kidnapped\nhim as a child, after all...
He said himself that ever since he\nescaped, his sole purpose in life has\nbeen to exact revenge on 'em.
In light'a the baggage he's luggin' around,\nwhat can a few schmucks like us even do?
Yes, I see what you mean. Couldn't we\nshow him a bit more leniency, Cleo?
But surely you realize that I'm always the\none cleaning up the messes around here.\nFurthermore, I— Hm?
It's just a little mouse.\nHeh, I didn't expect a yelp like that\nfrom you, Cleo. It was kinda cute.
Wh— Please do not tease me.
I heard a scream!\nDid a Syndicate lackey show up?!
O dragon sleeping within me,\ngrant me your POWEEEEEEERRR!
Where are those Syndicate goons?!\nLemme at 'em!
Dang, it looks like a bomb went off in here!\nGonna be a real job to clean this up.
What was that, Cleo?\nCouldn't hear you.
UNFORGIVABLE! My patience is WELL\npast its limit! You listen here, Aldred!
I sympathize with your circumstances,\nbut that does not give you free reign\nto vandalize the castle!
The reason you connect the Syndicate to\neverything is because it is the only lens\nthrough which you've ever seen the world.
And that, Aldred, is why you are going\nto learn about a little something called\nEVERYDAY LIFE!
Wh-what...?! *gasp*\nCould this be another Syndicate plot?!
And our first order of business will\nbe breaking you of THAT particular habit!
